`karr context --json` (and probably plain `karr context`) crashes:

```
Can't locate object method "strftime" via package "Sun May 24 01:41:12 2026" (perhaps you forgot to load "Sun May 24 01:41:12 2026"?) at /storage/raid/home/getty/perl5/lib/perl5/App/karr/Cmd/Context.pm line 190.
```

Looks like a scalar/object mixup — a localtime() string is being method-called as if it were a DateTime object. Likely:

```perl
my $dt = localtime();  # scalar context — returns string!
$dt->strftime(...);    # boom
```

Should be `my $dt = DateTime->now;` or `localtime()` in list context wrapped.

Reproduce: `karr init --name test && karr context --json` in any git repo.
